(508, 1, '2011-09-17 17:45:29', '2011-09-17 17:45:29', 'These are the people who really make the clinic run.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_439" align="alignnone" width="200" caption="Becky Coen - Office Manager"]<a href="http://www.pacedermatology.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/L1000255.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-439" title="Becky Coen" src="http://www.pacedermatology.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/L1000255-200x178.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="178" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nBecky Coen comes from a background of veterinary medicine. She spent many years working as an office manager at a large veterinary office in Puyallup. Now she has joined this medical clinic and brings a long list of crucial skills to the office.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_440" align="alignnone" width="200" caption="Shirley Tietz - Medical Assistant"]<a href="http://www.pacedermatology.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/L1000256.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-440" title="Shirley Tietz" src="http://www.pacedermatology.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/L1000256-200x166.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="166" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nShirley Tietz has spent many years as a dermatology medical assistant in Colorado. She moved to Washington to be closer to her family and has found Pace Dermatology where she can continue to practice the field she loves.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nStaucia Cullivan is the newest addition to the clinic. She comes from a background of primary care so dermatology is new to her but she is a fast learner and has been an asset to the clinic.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The Associates', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '84-revision-7', '', '', '2011-09-17 17:45:29', '2011-09-17 17:45:29', '', 84, 'http://www.pacedermatology.com/84-revision-7', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
