(536, 1, '2011-09-17 18:24:23', '2011-09-17 18:24:23', 'First of all, every procedure is performed by a board certified dermatologist.  We strive to provide cost effective anti-aging procedures that provide the most improvement, and with independent research studies, definitively proven to reverse the effects of aging.\r\n\r\n<strong>Botulinum Toxin for wrinkles</strong> -This is probably one of the most satisfying cosmetic procedures that can be performed.  This is better known as Botox and Dysport.  This works for the lines on the forehead and between the eyes, as well as crows feet and some lines on the lower face.  It can also be used to soften large chewing and cheek muscles and give the face a slimmer appearance.  It can help to give eyes a more rounded appearance.\r\n\r\n<strong>Injections and Fillers</strong> - Brand names of these products include Restylane, Perlane, Juvederm, Radiesse, and Sculptra.  These compounds include hyaluronic acid (HA), calcium hydroxyapatite, and poly-L-lactic acid.  They are primarily used to fill deeper lines around the mouth and provide a "liquid" face lift when injected in the cheeks, cheekbones, and temples.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sclerotherapy for leg veins</strong> - This can be very effective for the right person with leg veins.  Sotradecol, sodium tetradecyl sulfate (STS) is used to sclerose the veins and is FDA approved for this purpose.<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Chemical Peels</strong> - These are several different acids that can be applied.  The most commonly applied are glycolic and TCA.  They are used for fine lines of the face.  They can help to restore a youthful glow.  Finally, they can be used to treat acne scars.\r\n\r\n<strong>Acne Scar Treatment</strong> - This process will be tailored to the individual but often includes a combination of subscision (a process of undercutting the scar), fillers, and/or chemical peels.', 'Cosmetic', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '23-revision-12', '', '', '2011-09-17 18:24:23', '2011-09-17 18:24:23', '', 23, 'http://www.pacedermatology.com/23-revision-12', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
