(927, 2, '2012-11-05 15:11:35', '2012-11-05 22:11:35', 'If you have a tattoo you regret theres a good chance your dermatologist can get it removed but there are several factors that come into play. Studies show that it will be harder to remove if:\r\n\r\n1. Its large, covering over 12 inches.\r\n\r\n2. Its colorful, ink colors other than black or red are more difficult.\r\n\r\n3. Its old, more than 3 years.\r\n\r\n4. If you smoke, smoking impairs wound healing processes.\r\n\r\n5. If it is on your feet or legs.\r\n\r\nRead full article at <a href="http://www.freep.com/article/20120919/FEATURES08/120919015/1025/features">freep.com</a>', 'Think Before You Ink', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'think-before-you-ink', '', '', '2012-11-05 15:11:35', '2012-11-05 22:11:35', '', 0, 'http://www.pacedermatology.com/?p=927', 0, 'post', '', 0),
